Salmon with Pecan Coating

2 fillets, salmon
1/2 cup, olive oil
1/2 tsp, salt
1/4 cup, flour
1, egg, beaten
1/4 cup, pecan, finely chopped
1 cup, water

Preheat IP by selecting SAUTE. Add and heat the oil.

Season fillets with salt.

Dip fillets in the flour, then in whisked egg, then in pecans.

Add to the pot and brown the fish on both sides.

Press CANCEL to stop the SAUTE function.

Remove the salmon from the pot and place the steam rack in it. Pour in the water. Place fillets on rack.

Pressure cook on HIGH with timer set for 4 minutes.

When timer beeps use natural release for 10 minutes, then manual release.
